Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi and US President Donald Trump gave speeches at the "Howdy, Modi!" event in Houston, Texas. Modi praised Trump for his leadership and friendship, particularly in strengthening the economic relationship between India and the US. He highlighted the achievements of his government in areas such as sanitation, access to banking, and ease of doing business. Modi also spoke about India's decision to revoke Article 370, which granted special status to the region of Jammu and Kashmir, and emphasized the importance of fighting terrorism. Trump, in his speech, praised Modi's leadership and the progress made by India under his administration. He highlighted the economic successes of the US and India, including job creation, tax cuts, and energy independence. Trump also expressed his commitment to fighting terrorism and strengthening the security partnership between the two countries.